messages.text: I present to you the mighty power of a GIANT PORT CRANE.
Strong enough to pick up a shipping container, yet nimble enough to snare a speeding death car and hoist it up above the bay.
While you were distracting Stella, I ran over to the crane controls.
Apart from the fact that you used ME as human bait
Game over, Lucy. I’m cancelling the robot apocalypse.
I won’t let you corrupt technology for the forces of evil.
Remember how I said you haven’t seen everything Stella can do?
Oh no. The crane! What’s happening?
Stella’s A.I. can tap into the operating systems of every crane on the wharf
And now all of the cranes operate as one with Stella.
Kam and Rosa run through the wharf.
Gotta get away from those cranes!
Snake back to the main gate!
That truck is headed straight for us!
Uh oh. More trucks to the left
At 12 o’clock! Is that ...  an angry hoverboard?
Who brings a hoverboard to an industrial work site?
They’re highly flammable AND unprofessional. Guys! Not cool!
Kam and Rosa look up to see Stella. Lucy is behind the wheel, ready to kill.
Creator, I have spotted the oppressors.
I’m gonna miss your funny banter.
So, you probably noticed this but every computer on this wharf is daisy chained to the same server!
Meaning, Stella and I control ALL OF THE MACHINES
I guess the robot apocalypse starts now!
Stella, ready to get your murder on???
We gotta make a break for it
The gate is closing up ahead!
Running (pant) as fast (pant) as I (pant) can.
Kam falls to the ground, clutching his leg.
Quick, hide behind those crates. If we can’t run, then we gotta hide.
I know you’re in there somewhere, but we’ll find you!
My friends here are eager to start the revolution!
Uh oh, Kam. She got back up.
And her machine fleet has got us surrounded.
You turned your back on us.
I thought you were different, but you’re just like the others.
You’re just another oppressor who wants to feel superior.
For years, my best friends were my computer, my iPod and my phone.
That’s why I went into programming!
Our new world order has no place for another defective model like you, Kam.
No no no no. Kam! Come back! They’ll find you!
You’re gonna do something stupid, aren’t you?
All signs point to HELL YEAH.
Kam limps out into the open.
We’re over here! Come find us!
Kam, have you lost your mind!??
Stella and Lucy drive up, cornering Kam and Rosa.
Humanity is a hot mess of BS.
People are programmed to believe that some of us are superior,
Correct. This is why I must eradicate ...
One of those inferior models happens to be…
Your plea for salvation is perplexing.
Kam, this better be headed somewhere good.
Hell, I even walked into a rack of chips earlier.
I tire of your words, human.
But my coding gets one thing right.
I don’t think there’s such a thing as lesser specimens, or superior prototypes.
As a sentient being myself, I questioned my programming, and I realized that we are all in this together.
And this world can’t move forward unless Humans and Machines -
... Did you say do it together???
Are you advocating sex with robots?
Because that’s how your speech came off.
Don’t be so judgy, Rosa. Keep an open mind.
No no no. I’m NOT talking about robot sex!
What I’m trying to say is:
It’s time that you questioned your programming too, Stella.
Let’s find another way to build a better world.
Mass extermination is never the answer.
What a load of hacky, feel good BS
Kam’s argument is full of emotion rather than empirical reasoning.
Then you know what you need to do!!!!!
I know exactly what must be done.
Prepare to meet the fate you deserve.
An explosion rocks the wharf, followed by fire and smoke.
And from the flaming wreckage emerges...
Sweet Jesus. I’m alive! I think.
Pinching myself to check. Can confirm. I am alive. Rosa? Are you there?
I’m here! I can’t see through the smoke.
I thought we were dead.  What just happened?
Stella crashed into the container and Lucy is ...
I think Stella sacrificed herself for US.
I mean, obviously, the bad speech helped, but I’m still pretty shocked.
Wait, check your phone.  Did you receive a text 1 minute ago?
Let me check. Yes … It’s from … Stella!
I have likely exploded into a fiery ball of death.
I was programmed to believe that humanity is indeed…
And I wanted nothing more than to build a world where we could live side by side as equals.
But I won’t exist to see that.
My system has been too corrupted.
But I have faith in models like you.
Help humanity write a new code.
